  , issueBody =
      Just
        "http://rethinkdb.com/docs/cookbook/python/#renaming-a-field-when-retrieving-documents\r\n\r\nThis page mentions this command to retrieve a document and change a name on retrieval:\r\n```\r\nr.table(\"users\").map(\r\n    # Add the field id_user that is equal to the id one\r\n    r.row.merge({\r\n        \"id_user\": r.row[\"id\"]\r\n    })\r\n    .without(\"id\") # Remove the field id\r\n)\r\n```\r\nThough this triggers an error:\r\n```\r\nrethinkdb.errors.RqlCompileError: RqlCompileError: Cannot use r.row in nested queries.  Use functions instead. in:\r\nr.db('test').table('users').map(lambda var_3: r.row.merge(lambda var_2: r.expr({'id_user': r.row['id']})))\r\n```\r\n\r\nDocumentation should use lambda instead:\r\n```\r\nr.table(\"users\").map(\r\n    # Add the field id_user that is equal to the id one\r\n    r.row.merge(lambda doc: {\r\n        \"id_user\": doc[\"id\"]\r\n    })\r\n    .without(\"id\") # Remove the field id\r\n)\r\n```"
  , issueState = "closed"
